---
title: Zingy Mustard Soy Salmon with Pickled Scallions, Ginger Rice & Citrus Carrots
description: Fishing for a delicious, sea-faring meal? We’ve got just the thing: crispy salmon fillets drizzled with an ultra-flavorful sauce. In it, there’s sweet soy glaze, Dijon mustard, lime juice, and minced ginger. On the side, there’s roasted carrots tossed with lime zest and ginger-scented jasmine rice. The salmon is finished with a scattering of pickled scallion whites, crunchy scallion greens, and toasted sesame seeds. We think it’s safe to say you’ll fall for this dish hook, line, and sinker!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/603660b5f930d87dd914cb6e-dbf162fc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/zingy-mustard-soy-salmon-603660b5f930d87dd914cb6e-15281ec2.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/zingy-mustard-soy-salmon-603660b5f930d87dd914cb6e
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 930 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1450 mg
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{12%ounce} lengthwise; cut into 3-inch-long,
½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter
@lime{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{},
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Cover to keep
warm.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @white wine
vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt. Set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @teriyaki sauce{8%tablespoon}, remaining
ginger, a squeeze of lime juice, and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt
and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably #nonstick{}, over
medium-high heat. Add salmon skin sides down; cook until skin is lightly
browned and crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Carefully flip and cook until fish is
opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Transfer salmon to a #plate{}. Return pan to medium-high heat and add sauce.
Bring to a boil and cook until reduced by half, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and
pepper.

Toss carrots with lime zest to taste.

Divide rice, carrots, and salmon between plates; drizzle salmon with sauce.
Top with pickled scallion whites (draining first). Garnish with scallion
greens. Top with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and any remaining sriracha to
taste. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> We think it's safe to say you'll fall for this dish hook, line, and sinker!